<br>
1)  Turning up all graphics options to MAXIMUM using the sliders provided in game.  I subsequently reset them to the default &quot;medium&quot; setting.  (You can use one of about 8 or so default settings ranging from very low to very high or you can customize your own settings).<br>
<br>
2) Approaching a huge group of PC's near town while on medium setting.<br>
<br>
3) Resetting my keyboard command preferences (For some reason, everytime I scrolled through this particular options screen, everything in the background froze).<br>
<br>
My system isn't the greatest, but it isn't bad either.<br>
<br>
AMD Athlon 2.5 gig processor<br>
1024 Megs of DDR 333 RAM<br>
GeForce 4 Ti 4600 with 128 megs RAM graphics card.<br>
<br>
As for melees and money making...I have no idea.  I only made it to the end of the tutorial and into the newbie town.  I didn't even get to go gather resources or do any battle. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=perifv>PeriFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/10/03 3:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2170.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I started on Dawn today, too...</span><hr size=1> I'm starting to get hit by the lag bug. I'll walk into an area, and it takes a couple of seconds for the players and NPCs to show up. I could see where this would be a problem if I was in an area with enemies around me. <br>
